tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  19,29,"She pointed towards her son Jesus (peace be upon him) who was in the cradle. So the people said in surprise: “How can we talk to a child who is in the cradle?”"
  19,30,"Jesus (peace be upon him) said: “I am the servant of Allah. He gave me the Gospel and made me one of His prophets."
  19,31,"And He made me a great benefit for the servants wherever I am. And He ordered me to perform prayer and give Zakat for as long as I live."
  19,32,"And He made me righteous to my mother. And He did not make me arrogant towards the obedience of my Lord nor did He make me disobedient to her."